  "summary": "react-simple-utils-kit ships postinstall script combining child_process and outbound HTTP",
  "details": "Package executes postinstall.js automatically on `npm install`. The script imports child_process and performs an outbound HTTP POST. The combination of lifecycle-time auto-execution, child_process invocation, and network beaconing in a small utility-named package matches the structural fingerprint of an installer-side credential/host exfiltration dropper. The package name is also a generic 'utils kit' lure with no documented purpose justifying install-time network or subprocess activity.",
